In [63]:
def resize_images_create_y_target(X,y,images_dict):    
    for pet_name, images in images_dict.items():
        for image in images:
            img = cv2.imread(str(image))
            resized_img = cv2.resize(img,(180,180))
            X.append(resized_img)
            y.append(pets_labels_dict[pet_name])

Building the CNN model¶

In [86]:
## as the number of output clases are two cat and dog, we can use binary_crossentropy loss funciton.
## Also setting only one neuron in the final output layer becuase the output is binary cat or a dog

model = Sequential([
  layers.Conv2D(16, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'),
  layers.MaxPooling2D(),
  layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'),
  layers.MaxPooling2D(),
  layers.Conv2D(64, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'),
  layers.MaxPooling2D(),
  layers.Flatten(),
  layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
  layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),

  layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
# loss=tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True),

model.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])
              
model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train, epochs=30)

Using data augmentation technique to overcome overfitting and improve the prediction performance¶

In [94]:
img_height = 180
img_width = 180

data_augmentation = keras.Sequential(
  [
    layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomFlip("horizontal", 
                                                 input_shape=(img_height, 
                                                              img_width,
                                                              3)),
    layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomRotation(0.1),
    layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomZoom(0.1),
  ]
)

Build the model with data augmentation and drop out¶

In [103]:
model = Sequential([
  data_augmentation,
  layers.Conv2D(16, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'),
  layers.MaxPooling2D(),
  layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'),
  layers.MaxPooling2D(),
  layers.Conv2D(64, 3, padding='same', activation='relu'),
  layers.MaxPooling2D(),
  layers.Dropout(0.4),
  layers.Flatten(),
  layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),
  layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),

  layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
])
In [104]:
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
               loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])
              
model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train, epochs=30)
